  "prompt": "Why is Country Chicken (Desi Murga) tastier than Broiler Chicken?",
  "response": "Country Chicken (Desi Murga) is often considered tastier than Broiler Chicken for several reasons:\n\n1. Diet and Lifestyle\n- Country chickens eat a varied diet of grains, insects, and plants\n- They roam freely and have more natural movement\n- This diverse diet and active lifestyle contributes to better meat flavor\n\n2. Slower Growth\n- Desi Murga grows naturally and slowly (about 6-8 months)\n- Broiler chickens are bred to grow rapidly (around 6-7 weeks)\n- Slower growth allows better muscle development and flavor\n\n3. Meat Texture\n- Country chicken meat is firmer and less watery\n- More muscle development due to free-range lifestyle\n- Denser and more flavorful meat composition\n\n4. Muscle Fiber\n- More developed muscle fibers\n- Higher protein content\n- Better taste and nutritional profile\n\n5. Less Chemical Intervention\n- Fewer hormones and antibiotics\n- More organic and natural growth\n- Healthier meat with better taste\n\n6. Genetic Diversity\n- Traditional breed variations\n- Better genetic adaptability\n- More natural flavor characteristics\n\nThese factors contribute to the superior taste and quality of Country Chicken compared to Broiler Chicken.",
